article.description: DeAndre Haywood scored 12 points, including a basket as time expired and Delaware State edged past North Carolina A&T 55-53 on Saturday.
article.headline: Delaware State clips North Carolina A&T at buzzer, 55-53
article.linkText: Delaware State clips North Carolina A&T at buzzer, 55-53
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- DeAndre Haywood scored 12 points, including a basket as time expired and Delaware State edged past North Carolina A&T 55-53 on Saturday. N.C. A&T had led by as many as seven in the second half, but could not shake Delaware State, which tied it at 53-53 on a Devin Morgan 3-pointer with just under a minute to play. As snow and treacherous travel conditions forced postponement of three other Mid-East Athletic Conference games, N.C. A&T was eager to break a 13-game losing skid. Morgan scored 14 with four 3-pointers to lead the Hornets (4-12, 1-0), who snapped a four-game skid of their own, and Kavon Waller added 12, including three 3-pointers. Donte Watson scored a season-high 18 for the Aggies (1-14, 0-1), marking his return after missing nine games. Davaris McGowens scored 15 and grabbed 12 rebounds. The Aggies outrebounded Delaware State 43-24.
